<p>The <code>echo</code> tag evaluates and outputs expressions.</p>

<h2>Basic Arithmetic</h2>
<pre>{open}echo 5 + 3{close}
{open}echo 10 * 4{close}
{open}echo 100 / 5{close}
{open}echo 17 - 8{close}</pre>
<ul>
  <li>5 + 3 = {echo 5 + 3}</li>
  <li>10 * 4 = {echo 10 * 4}</li>
  <li>100 / 5 = {echo 100 / 5}</li>
  <li>17 - 8 = {echo 17 - 8}</li>
</ul>

<h2>With Variables</h2>
{set $price = 25}
{set $quantity = 4}
<pre>{open}set $price = 25{close}
{open}set $quantity = 4{close}
Total: {open}echo $price * $quantity{close}</pre>
<p>Total: {echo $price * $quantity}</p>

<h2>Complex Expressions</h2>
<pre>{open}echo (10 + 5) * 2{close}
{open}echo 100 - (20 * 3){close}</pre>
<ul>
  <li>(10 + 5) * 2 = {echo (10 + 5) * 2}</li>
  <li>100 - (20 * 3) = {echo 100 - (20 * 3)}</li>
</ul>

<h2>Pipe Functions with Echo</h2>
{set $value = 3.14159}
<pre>{open}set $value = 3.14159{close}
{open}echo $value | %.2f{close}</pre>
<p>Formatted: {echo $value | %.2f}</p>
